{"MIX":[{"def":"To cause a promiscuous interpenetration of the parts of, as of two or more substances with each other, or of one substance with others; to unite or blend into one mass or compound, as by stirring together; to mingle; to blend; as, to mix flour and salt; to mix wines.","pos":""},{"def":"To unite with in company; to join; to associate.","pos":""}],"MIXABLE":[{"def":"Capable of being mixed.","pos":""}],"MIXED":[{"def":"Formed by mixing; united; mingled; blended.","pos":""}],"MIXEDLY":[{"def":"In a mixed or mingled manner.","pos":""}],"MIXEN":[{"def":"A compost heap; a dunghill.","pos":""}],"MIXER":[{"def":"One who, or that which, mixes.","pos":""}],"MIXOGAMOUS":[{"def":"Pairing with several males; -- said of certain fishes of which several males accompany each female during spawning.","pos":""}],"MIXOLYDIAN MODE":[{"def":"The seventh ecclesiastical mode, whose scale commences on G.","pos":""},{"def":"Containing, or consisting of, lines of different kinds, as straight, curved, and the like; as, a mixtilinear angle, that is, an angle contained by a straight line and a curve.","pos":""}],"MIXTION":[{"def":"A kind of cement made of mastic, amber, etc.","pos":""}],"MIXTLY":[{"def":"With mixture; in a mixed manner; mixedly.","pos":""}],"MIXTURE":[{"def":"A kind of liquid medicine made up of many ingredients; esp.","pos":""},{"def":"A mass of two or more ingredients, the particles of which are separable, independent, and uncompounded with each other, no matter how thoroughly and finely commingled; -- contrasted with a compound; thus, gunpowder is a mechanical mixture of carbon, sulphur, and niter.","pos":""}]}